**Improving Timers and Logic**

I'm now separating core AI tasks from the main `update` method. I realized timers that affect state flags, like `isSprinting`, need to decrement every frame, not just when `updateLogic` runs. I'm moving general timer decrements to the "Always Run" block to ensure smooth state transitions. I'm also considering accepting that distant bots will change their minds less frequently as a natural effect of LOD, while ensuring that the visual experience still remains as smooth as possible.


